SIMPLE: rigger
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rigger
<hw>Rig"ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
rigs or dresses; one whose occupation is to fit the rigging of a
ship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A cylindrical pulley or drum in machinery.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Painting)</fld> <def>A long slender, and pointed
sable brush for making fine lines, etc.; -- said to be so called from
its use by marine painters for drawing the lines of the
rigging.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rigging</ent>⟦br⟧
